276
00:16:31,940 --> 00:16:34,600
Because it's poor.
Therefore, it has equality.

277
00:16:35,700 --> 00:16:37,060
And because it has equality,

278
00:16:37,540 --> 00:16:40,580
people there are united, right?

279
00:16:41,140 --> 00:16:42,400
They're not divided, they're united.

280
00:16:42,720 --> 00:16:46,580
And what else? They're obedient, right?

281
00:16:47,320 --> 00:16:49,220
They listen to what the
government tells them to do.

282
00:16:49,860 --> 00:16:51,600
And last thing is they're hungry.

283
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:56,160
They will work very hard for very little.

284
00:16:56,560 --> 00:16:59,180
Okay? Do you understand? So,

285
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:04,900
it is possible that in 20 years' time,

286
00:17:05,540 --> 00:17:07,840
North Korea overtakes South Korea.

287
00:17:08,360 --> 00:17:12,320
Because its people are willing to work
harder than the South Korean people.

288
00:17:12,840 --> 00:17:15,060
Okay? Does it make sense? So,

289
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:20,620
